Helper functions for metan

Tiago Olivoto

2019-12-24

Source: vignettes/vignettes_helper.Rmd
vignettes_helper.Rmd

Getting started

library(metan)
library(kableExtra) # Used to make the tables
library(tidyverse)
# Function to make HTML tables
print_table = function(table){
  kable(table, "html", digits = 3) %>%
    kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed", "responsive"),
                  font_size = 12)
}

Select helpers

The package metan reexports the tidy select helpers and implements three own select helpers based on operations with prefixes and suffixes: difference_var(), intersect_var(), and union_var().

  • Variables that start with a prefix and ends with a suffix.

Here, we will select the variables from data_ge2 that start with “C” and ends with “D”.

data_ge2 %>% 
  select(intersect_var("C", "D"))
# A tibble: 156 x 2
      CD  CDED
   <dbl> <dbl>
 1  16.3 0.538
 2  14.5 0.551
 3  16.4 0.561
 4  17.4 0.586

 6  17.5 0.577
 7  18.0 0.594
 8  17.2 0.608
 9  16.4 0.576
10  15.5 0.597
# … with 146 more rows
  • Variables that start with a prefix OR ends with a suffix.

The following code select variables that start with “C” or ends with “D”.

data_ge2 %>% 
  select(union_var("C", "D"))
# A tibble: 156 x 5

  • Variables that start with a prefix AND NOT ends with a suffix.

The following code select variables that start with “C” and not ends with “D”.

data_ge2 %>% 
  select(difference_var("C", "D"))

Bind cross-validation objects

AMMI0 <- cv_ammi(data_ge, ENV, GEN, REP, GY, naxis = 0)
AMMI2 <- cv_ammi(data_ge, ENV, GEN, REP, GY, naxis = 2)
AMMI9 <- cv_ammi(data_ge, ENV, GEN, REP, GY, naxis = 9)
AMMIF <- cv_ammif(data_ge, ENV, GEN, REP, GY)
BLUP_g <- cv_blup(data_ge, ENV, GEN, REP, GY)
bind1 <- bind_cv(AMMI0, AMMI2, AMMI9)
bind2 <- bind_cv(AMMI0, AMMI2, AMMI9, bind = "means")

g1 <- split_factors(data_ge, ENV)
